column1: # this file was last compared to a developer's (jwlm's) configuration on 7/30/14, all
# lines ending with # were verified, '<' means an earlier version was used by jwlm
# this upgraded Rcpp means that several later Zest packages must be upgraded in synch with it
# proto, gsubfn and chron needed by rjava, which is needed by sqldf, which is (for unexplained reasons!) needed by Underwriting
# sqldf sometimes needs to be built after DBI?
# we need to load these pkgs explicitly for lubridate: DBI, plyr, stringr, digest, memoise
# r-cran-matrix version-pinned debian package already installed during R config, so unspecified here
